                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/11/2003&nbsp;: 2:30:09 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Ssoul, helping Yag out a bit here but I have done the same situation as you there is no secret and I used Yag's methods that he mentioned(just made them up) but if you seriously get hit by a mob when you are solo'ing that isn't good bro.  <br /><br />I have solo'ed there fro 52 to 59 and only died twice, once was a severwide LD issue which I got a GM rez for.  And the other was a train from a bard... who I nicely repayed a couple hours later <img src="images/devil_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" />.  When I pull I usually start off with 80% hp and kill that mob with just Splurt/Pyro and a pet.  Then my next mob I will Splurt/Pyro/Vexing and the pattern continues between those two.  Trust me it creates a lot less down time then your waiting for the mob to die off.  Cause even if you have Dooming Darkness on the mob I have noticed that they can out regen that if you don't have your pet bashing his ass, which still takes quite a long time.  The only beneficial thing I can see of always having your hp full is that the mob will turn around at a closer percent.  When I am at 50% the mob usually doens't turn around until about 7% and then I can finally sit down and wait for DoT's to finish it off.  Otherwise when I am full hp it is usually aroun 15 - 19%.</span></font></td>
