              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Iskander</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/04/2003&nbsp;: 11:39:11 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Soloing without downtime is matter of patience, timing and lazines. You need to learn area you hunting in, learn mobs you hunting. Some areas and mobs cannot be done in this way. Then there are two key rules to remember:<br />1) Only apply enough DOTs to kill mob. Most folks tend to unload whole mana bar to kill mob in 30 sec and then med for 2 min. You can instead be killing mob for 2 min and then be ready to pull right away. If mob die too slow then ether you lack patience or mobs are too hard for you.<br />2) Sit to med every time there is possibility to do so. Your mana regen is increased and HP loss is decreased while sitting. When you fear kiting, just run before mob to keep it in spell range and sit till fear breaks (or you have to reapply something). When root rotting, just step away from mob and sit till root breaks. When aggro kiting, well... I am kinda iffy of aggro kiting with constant lag I have. Have yet to try it.<br /><br />Any way, following this easy rules you can pull non-stop till your eyes pop out, or you pull something extra while asleep, or druids come.</span></font></td>
